content: Printed line is thinner than desired.
name: Context1

content: Excess filament is squished upwards at the edges of the current printing line creating a rough surface and wavy patterns.
name: Context2

content: Filament is getting torn off the bed when the next neighbouring line is printed.
name: Context3

content: Finished prints are hard to remove from the print bed.
name: Context4

content: When looking at the bottom of your printed object, you can clearly make out individual lines with a noticeable gap between each line.
name: Context5

content: During printing the first layer, the individual lines are not touching each other.
name: Context6

content: There’s small gaps where the lines of the infill are not touching the outlines of the wall.
name: Context7

content: The shape of the extruding line is very round. With the proper distance, extruded line is slightly squished, pancake shaped.
name: Context8

content: Individual printed lines are barely sticking to the build plate.
name: Context9

content: Parts are warping off the build plate or become loose during the prints.
name: Context10

content: Your print is lifting off the bed, such as warping, or returning to your printer with a birds nest.
name: Context11

content: Nozzle too close to the bed
name: Context12

content: Nozzle too far away from the print bed
name: Context13

content: The left side of your nozzle is too close and the right side it is fine or even too high up, your bed is most likely at an angle – not level with the nozzle. Same goes for front and back and of course this can happen in both axis at the same time.
name: Context14

content: You see debris from a previous print, dust, gunk, spots, etc

name: Context16

content: You see some dents in the otherwise smooth bottom surface of a finished print.
name: Context17
